MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

91- 1855. Cope v. Dallman.

In Habeas Corpus. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a petition for a writ of habeas corpus. Upon consideration of petitioner’s application to dismiss,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that said application be, and the same is hereby, granted, effective September 26, 1991.

ACCORDINGLY, IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and hereby is, dismissed.
